%S A380887 1,400,525,644,759,864,972,1089,1188
%N A380887 a(n) is the smallest positive integer s such that n positive integers exist whose sum is s and whose product is s * 100^(n-1), or 0 if no such s exists.
%C A380887 In the case of a(n) > 0, the AGM inequality shows a(n) >= 100 * n^(n/(n-1)). This bound gives a(2) >= 400, a(3) >= 520, a(4) >= 635, a(5) >= 748, a(6) >= 859.
%C A380887 a(n) is 100 times the smallest price r such that n prices exist whose sum and product both are equal to r. For example (see Guardian article link) 7.11 = 1.20 + 1.25 + 1.50 + 3.16 = 1.20 * 1.25 * 1.50 * 3.16.
%H A380887 Alex Bellos, <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2025/feb/03/can-you-solve-it-sexy-maths">Can you solve it? Sexy maths</a>, 2. The 7-Eleven, The Guardian, 3 Feb 2025.
%e A380887 a(2) = 400 because 200 + 200 = 400 and 200 * 200 = 400 * 100^1 and no positive integer smaller than 400 exists with the requested properties. For a(3) the sum is 525 = 150 + 175 + 200, for a(4) it is 644 = 125 + 160 + 175 + 184, for a(5) it is 759 = 125 + 125 + 160 + 165 + 184.
%o A380887 (PARI) hasTuple(n, divs, currentTuple, currentSum, currentPro, targetSum, targetPro, i0) = {
%o A380887   my(newSum, newPro);
%o A380887   if(#currentTuple == n, return(currentSum == targetSum && currentPro == targetPro));
%o A380887   for(i = i0, #divs,
%o A380887     newSum = currentSum + divs[i];
%o A380887     newPro = currentPro * divs[i];
%o A380887     if(newSum <= targetSum && targetPro % newPro == 0,
%o A380887       if(hasTuple(n, divs, concat(currentTuple, [divs[i]]), newSum, newPro, targetSum, targetPro, i), return(1));
%o A380887     );
%o A380887   );
%o A380887   return(0);
%o A380887 }
%o A380887 hasSolution(n, targetSum) = {
%o A380887   my(targetPro = targetSum * 100^(n-1));
%o A380887   hasTuple(n, divisors(targetPro), [], 0, 1, targetSum, targetPro, 1);
%o A380887 };
%o A380887 a(n) = {
%o A380887   if(n == 1, return(1));
%o A380887   for(s = ceil(100 * n^(n/(n-1))), +oo, if(hasSolution(n, s), return(s)));
%o A380887 };
%o A380887 for (n = 1, 5, print(a(n)));
